<doc id="1045277" wikidata="Q5932544" url="?curid=1045277" title="Hugh Ross Williamson">
<text>Hugh Ross Williamson (1901–1978) was a prolific British popular historian, and a dramatist. Starting from a career in the literary world, and having a Nonconformist background, he became an Anglican priest in 1943.

In 1955 he converted to Roman Catholicism and wrote many historical works in a Catholic apologist tone. In 1956, he published his autobiography, &quot;The Walled Garden&quot;. Ross Williamson was critical of the reforms introduced by the Second Vatican Council.

